In [[computer science]], '''concurrency semantics''' is a way to give meaning to [[concurrent systems]] in a mathematically rigorous way. Concurrency semantics is often based on mathematical theories of concurrency such as various [[process calculi]], the [[actor model]], or [[Petri net]]s.

